Senior Associate
Responsibilities
What you'd do?Senior associate will be the leader at field work in handling compliance, tax dispute, tax due diligence, tax advisory, and audit support projects, including but not limited to:Participating in project planning, administration and economics, e.g., budgeting, staffing, billing, and time analysis.Playing active role in discussions and meetings, both with client and team, providing substantive input delivered at the appropriate time.Guiding team members on the application of standard Firm approaches and methodologies.Demonstrating importance of quality by reviewing work products of others to ensure a detail, accurate and timely mannered deliverables.Others as necessary, such as:Doing research and analysing tax issues.Preparing documents, i.e. client’s tax return, supporting documents, response letter for related parties RequirementsMinimum Bachelor Degree in Accounting/ Fiscal/ Finance/ EconomicsHas 3 -5 solid experience in Taxation areaGood adaptability in dynamic working environment.Eyes for details.Good team player and enjoy working collaboratively with people from variety of backgrounds.Good interpersonal and communication skillsProficient in English, both written and spoken
